<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Membership FAQs - Football Club</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheet/faq.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Navbar -->
  <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

  <main class="container mt-5 mb-5">
    <h1 class="faq-header">FAQ</h1>

    <!-- Membership Tier Tabs -->
    <ul class="nav nav-tabs" id="membershipTabs" role="tablist">
      <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
        <button class="nav-link active" id="gold-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#gold" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="gold" aria-selected="true">GOLD</button>
      </li>
      <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
        <button class="nav-link" id="silver-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#silver" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="silver" aria-selected="false">SILVER</button>
      </li>
      <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
        <button class="nav-link" id="bronze-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#bronze" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="bronze" aria-selected="false">BRONZE</button>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Tab Content -->
    <div class="tab-content" id="membershipTabsContent">
      <!-- Gold Tab -->
      <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="gold" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="gold-tab">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What priority do Gold members have over Silver and Bronze members?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Gold members have the highest priority for ticket sales, ballots, and exclusive events.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What are the exclusive benefits for Gold members?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Gold members enjoy exclusive VIP access to club events, priority ticket booking, 15% discount on merchandise, 3% cashback on eligible purchases, and access to premium seating areas.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Can Gold members access all club events?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes, Gold members have access to all club events, including exclusive VIP events that are not available to Silver or Bronze members.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Will Members be given a choice of what area/price range when they apply in the ballot?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes, Gold members will be given first choice of seating areas and price ranges when applying in the ballot system.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>How long will Members be given to pay for their tickets if they are successful in the ballot?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Gold members will have 48 hours to complete their purchase after being successful in the ballot.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Silver Tab -->
      <div class="tab-pane fade" id="silver" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="silver-tab">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What priority do Silver members have over Bronze members?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Silver members have earlier access to ballots and ticket sales than Bronze members.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What are the benefits of Silver membership?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Silver members receive 10% discount on merchandise, 2% cashback on eligible purchases, early access to ticket sales, and invitations to select club events.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Will there be a limit to how many match ballots a Member can enter across the course of the season?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Silver members can enter all available match ballots throughout the season, but priority will be given to Gold members first.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What is the average chance of success for a Member entering the ballot?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">The success rate varies by match popularity, but Silver members typically have a 40-60% chance of success in the ballot, depending on demand.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bronze Tab -->
      <div class="tab-pane fade" id="bronze" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="bronze-tab">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What are the benefits of Bronze membership?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">5% discount, 1% cashback, essential benefits, club newsletter.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Can Bronze members upgrade to Silver or Gold?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes, Bronze members can upgrade to Silver or Gold membership at any time during the season by paying the difference in membership fees.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What happens if there are seats remaining after the ballot because the number of applications is lower than the number of seats available?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">If seats remain available after the ballot, they will be offered to members on a first-come, first-served basis, with priority given to higher tier members.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>If a Member is successful in the ballot and is not able to attend, will we offer a refund?</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down faq-icon"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">No refunds are offered, but Bronze members can use the ticket exchange system to sell their ticket to another member if they cannot attend.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>

  <script>
    // Add click handlers for FAQ questions
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
      const faqQuestions = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-question');

      faqQuestions.forEach(question => {
        question.addEventListener('click', function() {
          // Toggle active class on the question
          this.classList.toggle('active');

          // Toggle display of the answer
          const answer = this.nextElementSibling;
          if (answer.style.display === 'block') {
            answer.style.display = 'none';
          } else {
            answer.style.display = 'block';
          }
        });
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
